The paper deals with video generation using GANs and incorporates RNNs for modeling motion dynamics. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses unsupervised pixel-wise dense predictions, which could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also mentions incorporating motion estimation, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE).
